[thinking] I'm considering what happens if a package is marked as exported—this means no `injectionBase` path. But what about when dealing with `localMock`? For the JDK, I need to determine if something is coming from the JDK, especially regarding `com.sun.tools`, which isn't part of the standard `java/javax` packages. I wonder if the `implementationTitle` gives clues. It might be helpful to test things out in `jshell`. If the title isn't "Java Runtime Environment," that could mean it's a non-JDK function, despite being in a module. This is intriguing!
