calMock`? For the JDK, I need to determine if something is coming from the JDK, especially regarding `com.sun.tools`, which isn't part of the standard `java/javax` packages. I wonder if the `implementationTitle` gives clues. It might be helpful to test things out in `jshell`. If the title isn't \"Java Runtime Environment,\" that could mean it's a non-JDK function, despite being in a module. This is intriguing!", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0834da44b1b700280169f9716d1abc81a1b39b6c2365effc9e\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp-XGAVmWv9-63mEXzNvABoXDKXEt0Z5pLBtB-aVDnJ9PVInQqoQLO3n1-YzDPwKECipvmw9DCCX0CFsHsLRrAhyx_wWI4EzHf0H2WJmVtHBznzMRYgOZi4tfHMi9gtjGq_sKi97V386nfhmQ_jlr95kROxTT5-B4tp6cpe69EyHk8Q5ua2LaTSMOZ4qLbJKo9ldwCHe9aZ7nXNMi8yu-_sICSy1yoji64CpP5iC9pohxwM0mU8cbZ72ecwjxLwrEGT6ikAmNFyyFtlx-uVL8dAifsd_u2GXpP-K9KGd_bMiVu_rKIb_0J6FY3l1sKMgcI_2RWVXOoIebRrUDbAeHXQ2KLTIYJwpDDohcgocvFWKmfnbNhQKjPAHbq3GFLo9ojcKDMlkjsvwjdIWBtavgHzc4L_mOs4IT_EmU8nhUrSZXWCRmoG-1ySrl_uNif2WmXNenzKqLbO_ImuvvCm3ZXRHcP5icslBDL3vDhdnl4fXI7jTVFi02GHsCKhQB_znCYH_wsiaDpljFxQZ1lVsYYyelbXPWLZ602ntTjq9vkzu8xhISeQzJqJLr0IuBohn9gzLgPM6eqsP_oNfcvPACrxWXb4uoO61Glc4ZI6dJ9gpWydqc1tOkjH8pseZnwxA7MzMb5mbF66Wu2roPQ1pMJDhzaGWabICIK0m3L5bpt_a6zkS24ODCOyvZsBrd4PjClgPCcTQ997eytTI0dDwvBm7cRE_XnzKlzLRrxyCNyqlNQsu82tcgi_07NGWXoqWfr8DBrVy4_tGTfq544u7YGLAo3OHS54PeYhY8N-9R0ALYecxTU5TCVHwTLRHksC96vysPDyw6zC6tEaxcf9m-OyenyVrmdhEhzawL5bSSZ4UvFsM8KI5oZZl1zapcA-4sVUuRssCLNrHPBhiVVNCuxYoXAVnqMDN8W4y8450AxAmk62Ns3il9ZwwcwhEj_POrY4EdCKd5CBrK-MDDImKVtRPVm0MkbKgTsiGo3cihAEGG29dIdFSKo_StuqVFRnwuVBgxjx6z59mythKxWhUG2m_9QXZiESTvSqdv1A2CGdtwxCCqIH96I7x9D6ELK1OP3i7fmDcINgdme5wlqzcNAipp3-QNRWylflUnTfxGFu1WT24B4vkCeok3B04HFd5nx5KNXPyqMYaj2bKw9soGnx9ZF8DxvPwa5oSwArwfymlXzCovAyW6q4ml8aAHP2jD5QWGawdzkBkIBmkG4OClm6N6mjD7L9b4OogJOiXkakK7Voda9f_3dipOUuf-u3DiUl14-9yhELloOrdUb3D1brY-M9VLsrfSGNeSrxUKqO2960FKzeYI0U2Rpc0T3P1HuRnxrcKlNZZfY94GtYfE0uEtsWpoVzspMb3dE-LUQYFQ_g5tsZ3N18RiDhcCH40NTSW4P1YW27xHGlTYO-_Cpz-WMGczcliibB