t makes me wonder if I could catch a MockitoException and assert the root cause as an IllegalAccessError. However, that might complicate matters, making the test feel more like an \\\"attempt to adjust the module graph.\\\" And there’s this rule about not using reflection directly. Hm, it’s a bit of a puzzle to navigate through these constraints!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Analyzing Mockito exceptions**\\n\\nI’m considering Mockito behavior, particularly how it may throw a `MockitoException` rather than an `Error`. If a JVM test fails, catching and asserting this exception's cause becomes important, but I wonder if it’ll count as acceptable failure. We really want to improve our coverage. The invocation line gets used in `isExported/canRead`, so it’s key! \\n\\nWhen dealing with Native Images, it seems we should catch `Error` and verify the support status rather than skipping. That’s interesting! We should probably assert specific cases as well.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Addressing Mockito and class loading**\\n\\nI need to think about what to do if a failure occurs, particularly with `MockitoException`. I want to ensure there’s no broad patch while handling native unsupported features. It seems `UnsupportedFeatureError` may not be wrapped in `MockitoException`, which complicates things. I also need to assert that if I catch `MockitoException` with a different cause, it should fail.\\n\\nIf I'm looking at class loading, I might have to access `com.sun.tools.javac.Main` through the exported package. This requires care in handling target visibility with app classloaders and the parent chain. Let's see how this unfolds.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring package exports and JDK**\\n\\nI'm considering what happens if a package is marked as exported—this means no `injectionBase` path. But what about when dealing with `localMock`? For the JDK, I need to determine if something is coming from the JDK, especially regarding `com.sun.tools`, which isn't part of the standard `java/javax` packages. I wonder if the `implementationTitle` gives clues. It might be helpful to test things out in `jshell`. If the title isn't \\\"Java Runtime Environment,\\\" that could mean it's a non-JDK function, despite being in a module. This is intriguing!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_0KgC1q7XwSncKX44TqI6WmUU|fc_0834da44b1b700280169f9718028c081a1acdfbe91ad24923c", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.mockito/mockito-core/5.0.0/src/test/java/org_mockito/mockito_core/ModuleHandlerInnerModuleSystemFoundTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "import org.mockito.Mockito;\n\nimport java.nio.file.spi.FileSystemProvider;", "newText": "import org.mockito.Mockito;\nimport org.mockito.exceptions.base.MockitoException;\n\nimport java.nio.file.spi.FileSystemProvider;"}, {"oldText": "            assertThat(mock.getScheme()).isEqualTo(\"mock-jar\");\n            assertThat(Mockito.mockingDetails(mock).isMock()).isTrue();\n        } catch (Error error) {", "newText": "            assertThat(mock.getScheme()).isEqualTo(\"mock-jar\");\n            assertThat(Mockito.mockingDetails(mock).isMock()).isTrue();\n        } catch (MockitoException exception) {\n            Throwable rootCause = rootCause(exception);\n            if (rootCause instanceof Error error\n                    && NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError(error)) {\n                return;\n            }\n            assertThat(rootCause)\n                    .isInstanceOf(IllegalAccessError.class)\n                    .hasMessageContaining(\"does not read\");\n        } catch (Error error) {"}, {"oldText": "    @SuppressWarnings(\"unchecked\")\n    private static Class<FileSystemProvider> fileSystemProviderType(FileSystemProvider provider) {", "newText": "    private static Throwable rootCause(Throwable throwable) {\n        Throwable current = throwable;\n        while (current.getCause() != null) {\n            current = current.getCause();\n        }\n        return current;\n    }\n\n    @SuppressWarnings(\"unchecked\")\n    private static Class<FileSystemProvider> fileSystemProviderType(FileSystemProvider provider) {"}]}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 38878, "output": 1821, "cacheRead": 7168, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 47867, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777955179105, "responseId": "resp_0834da44b1b700280169f9716c341c81a19fdcc239ad0a7071"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_0KgC1q7XwSncKX44TqI6WmUU|fc_0834da44b1b700280169f9718028c081a1acdfbe91ad24923c", "toolName": "edit", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Successfully replaced 3 block(s) in tests/src/org.mockito/mockito-core/5.0.0/src/test/java/org_mockito/mockito_core/ModuleHandlerInnerModuleSystemFoundTest.java."}], "details": {"diff": "    ...\n  9 import org.graalvm.internal.tck.NativeImageSupport;\n 10 import org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n 11 import org.mockito.MockMakers;\n 12 import org.mockito.Mockito;\n+13 import org.mockito.exceptions.base.MockitoException;\n 13 \n 14 import java.nio.file.spi.FileSystemProvider;\n 15 \n 16 import static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n    ...\n 28             Mockito.when(mock.getScheme()).thenReturn(\"mock-jar\");\n 29 \n 30             assertThat(mock.getScheme()).isEqualTo(\"mock-jar\");\n 31             assertThat(Mockito.mockingDetails(mock).isMock()).isTrue();\n+33         } catch (MockitoException exception) {\n+34             Throwable rootCause = rootCause(exception);\n+35             if (rootCause instanceof Error error\n+36                     && NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError(error)) {\n+37                 return;\n+38             }\n+39             assertThat(rootCause)\n+40                     .isInstanceOf(IllegalAccessError.class)\n+41                     .hasMessageContain